<s docid="AP890309-0143" num="11" wdcount="29"> The Democratic-controlled Senate
today rejected the nomination of former Texas Sen. John Tower as defense
secretary, delivering a major rebuke to President Bush just 49 days into his
term.</s>

<s docid="AP890309-0143" num="12" wdcount="26"> The Senate's 53-47 vote came after
a bitter and divisive debate focused on Tower's drinking habits, behavior
